com.github.ilyes4j.gwt.mdl.components

Interface IUpgrade

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IMenu, IMenuCombo, ISlider
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Button, ButtonBase, Checkbox, CheckboxBase, CheckBoxStyleOperator, Dropdown, ExpandingTextField, Flip, FlipStyleOperator, Menu, MenuCombo, MultilineTextField, PasswordField, RadioButton, RadioStyleOperator, SingleLineTextField, Slider, SliderInput, TextField, TextfieldBase, ToggleStyleOperator, Tooltip, UpgradeHelper

    public interface IUpgrade
    An MDL component implements the IUpgrade interface to indicate that it can be upgraded. The upgrade means applying javascript behaviors and effects on the component. An upgradable component is upgraded when upgrade() is invoked.
    Author:
    Mohamed Ilyes DIMASSI
